[00:00.00]
[00:15.50]The sun was heavy on my shoulders today,
[00:20.50]Watching the hours slowly drift away.
[00:27.50]Through the heat and the dust and the pouring sweat,
[00:33.50]I kept a promise I haven't broken yet.
[00:40.00]But as the shadows start to stretch and lean,
[00:46.50]I’m headed back to the life unseen.
[00:52.50]When I see the light in the window pane,
[00:57.50]I forget the struggle and I forget the pain.
[01:04.00]Just to hear your laughter at the open door,
[01:10.00]I don’t feel the weight of the day anymore.
[01:17.00]In this quiet house, where our hearts are free,
[01:23.50]It’s a little piece of heaven here with me.
[01:45.00]The gold is fading into evening blue,
[01:50.50]And every step leads me closer to you.
[01:57.00]To see a mother’s smile and a child’s bright eyes,
[02:03.00]Is the greatest comfort and the greatest prize.
[02:09.50]The world outside can be loud and cold,
[02:16.00]But here is a story that never grows old.
[02:22.50]It’s more than a roof, it’s a blessing we share,
[02:28.50]In every soft word and in every prayer.
[02:35.00]No matter how weary the road might be,
[02:41.00]You are the sanctuary waiting for me.
[02:47.50]When I see the light in the window pane,
[02:53.00]I forget the struggle and I forget the pain.
[02:59.50]Just to hear your laughter at the open door,
[03:05.50]I don’t feel the weight of the day anymore.
[03:12.50]In this quiet house, where our hearts are free,
